I began to understand that a human being is not a \hich\f35 \lquote \loch\f35 machine\hich\f35 \rquote \loch\f35  in the traditional sense of the word.  Up and until this point, I had always seen myself as \hich\f35 \lquote \loch\f35 broken\hich\f35 
\rquote \loch\f35  and needing to be fixed.  The problem with seeing out bodies as just \hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 a machine is that we tend to reference it with the machines that we are accustomed to. 
