\par \hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 On January 18, 1990, Matthew C. Manning was given a devastating diagnosis of being HIV positive. By late 1993, he was diagnosed with full-blown AIDS and was hospitalized. Matt was faced with certa
\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 in death.  Then in mid-January, 1994, his AIDS went into a state of remission. On December 5th, 1994, Matt was diagnosed for the first time HIV negative and has consistently tested HIV negative since that time. 
\par \hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 In another independent review of this same s\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 pecific incident, the author writes: 
\par }\pard \s16\ql \li0\ri330\sa243\sl231\slmult0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin330\lin0\itap0 {\f35\cf1\insrsid15877736\charrsid9255237 \loch\af35\dbch\af13\hich\f35 \'93\loch\f35 Matthew Manning\hich\f35 \rquote \loch\f35 
s military physicians were unavailable for comment, so I asked Dr. Michael Thompson to review Matthew's medical records. 
\par }\pard \s16\ql \li0\ri0\sa243\sl233\slmult0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f35\cf1\insrsid15877736\charrsid9255237 \hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 "This patient, Matthew Manni\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 \hich\f35 
ng, was HIV-positive," says Dr. Thompson, reviewing Matthew's records.\'94\loch\f35 
 He had the regular test that we always do. Then, the story changes here. In 1994, after having AIDS, he had an opportunistic infection and then the tests are coming back negative. I a\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 s\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 
ked a couple of experts, infectious disease doctors, from Duke and other places. I said, 'Have you heard of anything like this where a person had HIV, went into AIDS, then the symptoms went into remission, and now they test HIV-negative, consistently HIV-
\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 n\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 egative since 1994? They had never heard of anything like this in the adult population. There is no medical explanation for this." 
