In 1997 Freddy and his family were on their way to the US and met, among others, two young women (from Rwanda) who were also coming to the US through the same program. 
\par }\pard \s16\ql \li0\ri190\sa243\sl231\slmult0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin190\lin0\itap0 {\f35\cf1\insrsid15877736\charrsid9255237 \hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 So\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 
me days after that, they all had to go through the physical examination required by the US immigration, for all who intend to come in as permanent residents. The examination, conducted by a doctor who got his MD from Johns Hopkins University, includes an 
\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 H\hich\af35\dbch\af13\loch\f35 IV test. Eugenie and her friend (two young women from Rwanda) tested positive.  
